  <div class="article-main">
    <article
      class="article-main-column main-column"
      itemscope
      itemtype="http://schema.org/Article"
    >
      <div class="article-top">
                  <div itemprop="description" class="element-hidden">From social media to constant email, it seems like our smartphones are running our lives. Here are some legit reasons why people are “unplugging” from technology and why it might be a good idea for you too.</div>
                <header class="article-header">
          <div class="group-article-meta">
            <div
  class="field field-name-post-date"
  itemprop="datePublished"
  content="2015-06-24"
>
  June 24, 2015  <span class="separator">|</span> </div>
            <div class="field article-author-top" itemscope itemprop="author" itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
  <span class="label">By </span>
    <a
    href="http://greatist.com/p/sophia-breene"
    title="User profile of "
    class="username"
    about="http://greatist.com/p/sophia-breene"
    typeof="sioc:UserAccount"
    itemprop="url"
  >
    <span itemprop="name">Sophia Breene</span>
  </a>
   </div>
          </div>
          <h1 class="title" id="page-title" itemprop="name headline alternativeHeadline">Why Everyone Should Unplug More Often</h1>
        </header>
        <div class="top-share">
          <div class="group_share" data-recirc-section>
  <div class="share-buttons icons" data-origin="top">
    <div ng-controller="socialCtrl"
